<div class="page">
  <h1>Legal Research and Case Management</h1>
  <p>The terminal turns out to be a surprisingly effective interface for legal work. The <a class="repo-link" href="/?category=legal">Legal</a> category includes workspaces for tracking cases, analysing evidence, and building forensic timelines.</p>
  <p>The <a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-case-file/">Claude Case File</a> workspace provides structured case management with Claude handling document organisation, timeline construction, and cross-referencing. <a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-evidence-assistant/">Claude Evidence Assistant</a> focuses specifically on evidence handling and chain-of-custody documentation. And <a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-code-lawyer/">Claude Code Lawyer</a> provides a more general legal research interface.</p>
  <p>The <a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-legal-aid-clinic/">Claude Legal Aid Clinic</a> explores an interesting angle: using Claude as a first-pass legal aid tool that can help people understand their rights and options before engaging professional counsel.</p>
  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;"><a href="/?category=legal" style="font-weight: 500;">Browse all Legal repositories &rarr;</a></div>
</div>
